ppens is, --i've done this before....whoever has CDok pipe turns in, and then KC pipe (or whichever) but when he turns in that robe he will get the RoTW, so the people with the pipes have to go first, then he turns in the robe last and will be awarded Robe of the whistling fist, but he MUST go last, other wise one of them will get it, so make him tell them &quot;okay tell me when you handed it in&quot; and dont make him him hand anything in until they said okay, hopefully he wont be jipped but thats how you do it.<br><br><br> <p>Wyndwolfe StormrunnerHierophant of Wr@ithQuellious Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/ujudustpriest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Judust Priest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(9/9/02 6:57:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/fwraith27960general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ALL EPIC MONKS PLS READ!!!</span><hr size=1> Ok thanks Wynd I had no idea how to MQ with 3 people.<br><br>Judust Priiest <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub75.ezboard.com/uorodruin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orodruin1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Reviv Officer</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(9/9/02 9:03:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub75.ezboard.com/fwraith27960general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ALL EPIC MONKS PLS READ!!!</span><hr size=1> Can be done, but beware.  The NPC you give the items to has to be charmed.  If you use anything but a fixed duration charm, you run the risk of losing part or all of the components if the charm breaks early.  Turn in the 2 pipes, have charm break, and you can wave good bye to the pipes, so you're going to have to be fast.  At least if you're holding all the pieces yourself, you can put all 3 items in the trade window and con him immediately before you hit the trade button.<br><br>Perhaps more importantly, beware of people trying to sell MQs of the pipes.  Friends and I camped Chardok for about 80 hours over the course of two or three months and I was getting incredibly frustrated during my epic chase.  I found someone selling the MQ of the Chardok pipe for 25K.  I agonized over it for a bit, then decided to pass on the offer.  Another monk I know took them up on the offer, and the individual was a scammer.  He took the cash, SAID he turned in the pipe (there's no message for each piece handed to Brother Balatin), then after my friend turned in his pipe and robe and didn't get item, the scammer turned in his pipe, received the robe, and immediately went LD. <p><I>"Increase my killing power, eh?"<BR> --Homer Simpson<BR></I><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67011" target="_blank">Aesir</a> - 60 Monk<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67138" target="_blank">Orodruin</a> - 59 Necromancer <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67027" target="_blank">Anjar</a> - 55 Shaman<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68537" target="_blank">Geien</a> - 51 Druid <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82039" target="_blank">Moren</a> - 41 Bard<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82031" target="_blank">Daemok</a> - 40 Rogue <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=228751" target="_blank">Orod</a> - 25 Magician <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=228756" target="_blank">Erebor</a> - 20 Warrior <BR><a href="http://www.pawns-of-chaos.com/reviv/" target="_blank">Reviviscence Guild</a>, Quell